We followed up the mechanism of the reaction by HRTEM for three samples of the nanocomposite that were picked up at different intervals (3.5, 8.5, and 15 minutes) from the beginning of sonication, as shown in Fig. 15. HRTEM investigation reveals that hexagonal ZnO nanorods ‘with pencil like tip’ are crosslinked together by PMA anions148 and self-assembled to nanoplatelets with grain boundaries as shown in Fig. 15(a1,2 and b1,2,3). From one perspective, as the temperature increases, crosslinking ZnO nanorods experienced a thermal expansion parallel (α∥c\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
