				\begin{document}$${\alpha }_{\perp }c$$\end{document}) to c-axis with a difference in factor nearly equal to 1.6, as the thermal expansion coefficients (α) are strongly direction-dependent149. Under this condition, the thermal energy that was produced by sonication was not enough for complete fusion and some nanorods can be disconnected as shown in Fig. 15(c3). Deposition of Mo8O23-MoO2 mixed oxide over fused-thermally expanded ZnO nanorods guarantees the adhesion of its hexagonal structure and hinders the grain boundaries as shown in Fig. 15(c1,2)150, 151. More detailed HRTEM images are in (Supplementary Figure S9). A brief schematic illustration for proposed morphology transition mechanism is shown in Fig. 16.Figure 15
